caption: this is the honest review you’re looking for, the food is pretty tasty, ill give them that but sometimes they never have the food i order, its always something up, sometimes i order and don't get my correct order. Very unprofessional and its get annoying sometimes.But their food is good enough to make u wanna keep buying from them.They just have a-lot to work on tho.I recommend calling before ordering online just to check if the food they have on their menu still available.
First time ordering here! Looks delicious tho 😋😋

I ordered fried turkey it said it came with all that’s in the description and I only received ONLY fried turkey I want my money back. The lady wants me to order more food from Uber to get what I’m missing from my order.
Good tasting Haitian foods that brings you back. Back with the goods taste and also long wait times. Got the fried fish with rice which was pretty good.

Thank you Enjoy EAT!!!! Your food is amazing and tasteful. I have to honestly say this is by far one of the best tasting Haitian food restaurants out there. The delivery time was right on target, the sealing of the bags was a nice touch. The jus grenadia and the boullion I ordered was perfect(the flavor was perfect and the spices were right on point). Overall, I have to say you guys Rock! Please keep making great food and monitor closely your customer service. I definitely will come back.

I ordered griot fritay from Uber eats which should include fried pork , marinad, sweet potato, plantain , akra & pikliz. It cost $12. They sent my food without plantain, marinad , sweet potato and pikliz. I literally only got sausage, griot & akra. They didn’t send a notes or anything , they just sent it like nothing was wrong. Very dishonest and I’m highly annoyed.

Hands down - this place REALLY does make the absolute best Haitian food in New York state, period.  People who love Haitian food usually get pretty passionate about who they think makes the best Haitian food.  Enjoy Eat puts that debate to rest.  Legume Beef - delicious!  Soup Joumou - BEYOND delicious!  Even their rice (white or rice with beans - doesn't matter) is incredible!!!!  Haven't tried every thing on their menu yet but I'll work my way through it since they make no mistakes.  Enjoy Eat, you have a customer for life now.  I can't imagine ordering Haitian food from anywhere else.  It would be subpar.
